Document Driven Development

This project includes an independently modified conversational design workflow
inspired by the Superpowers project by Jesse Vincent:
https://github.com/obra/superpowers

The retained ideas are: inspect project context first, ask one question at a
time, present 2-3 approaches with trade-offs, validate designs incrementally,
and require explicit user approval before implementation.

This plugin changes that workflow by dynamically discovering a project-specific
document graph, authoring and approving artifacts individually, and installing
document hashes, context locks, traceability checks, hooks, and CI gates.

This project is not affiliated with or endorsed by the Superpowers project.

The locked-plan debate, work-package decomposition, isolated implementation,
cross-review, bounded fix, and escalation concepts are independently adapted
from the former build flow in model-council:
https://github.com/minchanpark/model-council
Copyright (c) 2026 NewDawn

Document Driven Development does not require model-council at runtime. The
adapted provider runner and orchestration contracts are maintained independently
under this project's document-first safety and approval model.

The minimum-correct implementation decision ladder is adapted from Ponytail:
https://github.com/DietrichGebert/ponytail
Copyright (c) 2026 DietrichGebert

Document Driven Development does not require Ponytail at runtime and does not
copy its lifecycle hooks or full always-on instruction body. The adapted policy
is maintained under this project's document locks, safety gates, and compact
prompt budget.

